abstract.text: AppSync provides API actions for creating and interacting with data sources using GraphQL from your application.
Creates a Resolver object. A resolver converts incoming requests into a format that a data source can understand, and converts the data sourceâ€™s responses into GraphQL.
AppSync provides API actions for creating and interacting with data sources using GraphQL from your application.
Updates the cache for the GraphQL API.
Creates a Function object. A function is a reusable entity. You can use multiple functions to compose the resolver logic.

Evaluates a given template and returns the response. The mapping template can be a request or response template. Request templates take the incoming request after a GraphQL operation is parsed and convert it into a request configuration for the selected data source operation. Response templates interpret responses from the data source and map it to the shape of the GraphQL field output type. Mapping templates are written in the Apache Velocity Template Language (VTL).

Evaluates the given code and returns the response. The code definition requirements depend on the specified runtime. For APPSYNC_JS runtimes, the code defines the request and response functions. The request function takes the incoming request after a GraphQL operation is parsed and converts it into a request configuration for the selected data source operation. The response function interprets responses from the data source and maps it to the shape of the GraphQL field output type.
Lists the data sources for a given API.
Retrieves the current status of a schema creation operation.
Tags a resource with user-supplied tags.
Lists the types for a given API.
Maps an endpoint to your custom domain.
Updates an API key. You can update the key as long as itâ€™s not deleted.
List the resolvers that are associated with a specific function.
Creates a cache for the GraphQL API.

Lists the API keys for a given API. API keys are deleted automatically 60 days after they expire. However, they may still be included in the response until they have actually been deleted. You can safely call DeleteApiKey to manually delete a key before itâ€™s automatically deleted.
Retrieves the introspection schema for a GraphQL API.
Lists the resolvers for a given API and type.
Removes an ApiAssociation object from a custom domain.
Adds a new schema to your GraphQL API. This operation is asynchronous. Use to determine when it has completed.
Creates a unique key that you can distribute to clients who invoke your API.
Lists the tags for a resource.
